external_knowledge:
- The top 3 most expensive services refer to those with the highest costs, regardless of whether they are in-network or out-of-network; 
- A medical event can have multiple services, and the top 3 most expensive services are determined within each event; 
- In-network costs apply when patients receive care from healthcare providers within their health insurance network, while out-of-network costs apply when they receive care from providers outside their network.

sql:
SELECT s.service_name
FROM services s
JOIN providers p ON s.service_id = p.provider_id
WHERE p.rating = (
    SELECT MAX(rating) FROM providers
);
